        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/3d9bf3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-11-11T23:30:41.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"William Kelley\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n William Kelley:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A bit surprised that you seem to have appreciated the '05 Comte Armand so much. Paul opened a bottle blind after we tasted the '15s together last year and I was shocked at how dominated by high toast oak it was, all espresso and bacon fat. Did the wood seem integrated to you?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yeah, I usually don\u2019t get all that excited about this wine\u2013not usually my cup of tea\u2013too much of everything including oak, but the 05 at least on this night was very good and the oak surprisingly well integrated.  (we have a bunch of oak sensitive folks in the group, too, and no one was complaining.</p>",
